# TO INSTALL PYTHON
 
  #### THIS WORKS AS OF 8-15-19 ON WINDOWS
 
* GO TO python.org AND SELECT THE "DOWNLOADS" tab from the top menu.
* SELECT THE LATEST VERSION FOR WINDOWS (MINE IS PYTHON 3.7.4), THIS SHOULD APPEAR AS A YELLOW BUTTON UNDER THE MENU
* FOLLOW THE SETUP WIZARD TO INSTALL.
* NOW OPEN "CMD" (COMMAND PROMPT) ON YOUR COMPUTER.  ON WINDOWS 10 YOU CAN JUST TYPE "CMD" INTO THE SEARCH BAR AT THE BOTTOM OF THE SCREEN
* TYPE "python" INTO THE COMMAND LINE.  YOU SHOULD GET SOMETHING LIKE THIS:
```
C:\Users\*your-name-here*>python
Python 3.7.3 (v3.7.3:ef4ec6ed12, Mar 25 2019, 21:26:53) [MSC v.1916 32 bit (Intel)] on win32
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information. 
>>>
```

#### IF YOU DONT GET THE ABOVE CODE FOLLOW THE ENVIRONMENTAL SETUP STEPS BELOW.  IF EVERYTHING INSTALL CORRECTLY, THEN SKIP THE NEXT TUIT...
